<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1221,1695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,320,1594,1620]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Remarks:</emphasis>
This genus is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirkaldy" authorityName="Kirkaldy" box="[675,872,1594,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Flatidae" genus="Geisha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[675,758,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Geisha</emphasis>
Kirkaldy
</taxonomicName>
in appearance, but it can be distinguished from the latter by the shape of frons, the U-shaped carina and the costal membrane as wide as costal cell or a little wider.
</paragraph>
